title: Big Ten football Week 5 schedule (TV, times, live stream info)
text:
Comments 
Rutgers and Penn State got Big Ten play started two weeks ago, but now the rest of the conference will start matching up head-to-head beginning this weekend. 
The flipping of the calendar to October means that non-conference play is over for most teams throughout the country, and this Saturday's slate will see 12 Big Ten foes squaring off head-to-head. 
While Rutgers is enjoying its first and only bye of the season, the marquee game of the day will see top-ranked Ohio State traveling to Indiana for a 3:30 p.m. clash between 4-0 teams. 
Bidding to repeat as conference champions for the first time since finishing atop the league for five straight years from 2005-09, the Buckeyes enter conference play riding a Big Ten record 24-game conference winning streak. 
PLUS: NJ.com's Week 4 Big Ten power rankings: Here comes Michigan ... 
In all, four Big Ten teams sit unblemished after the first month of the season, including No. 2 Michigan State and No. 16 Northwestern. 
Ohio State and Northwesten are both off to their best start since 2010, Michigan State since 2010, Iowa since 2009 and Indiana since 1990.
